-- Avon's New CEO, AOL Patent Deal for $1.056B
-- B y
-- 2012-04-09T11:29:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-09/avon-s-new-ceo-aol-patent-deal-for-1-056b.html
Bloomberg's Dominic Chu reports 
that  Avon Products Inc. (AVP)  said Sherilyn “Sheri” McCoy has 
been named chief executive officer, effective April 23, and 
will join the cosmetics maker’s board. Also,      AOL Inc. (AOL)  
said it agreed to sell more than 800 of its patents and related 
patent applications to  Microsoft Corp. (MSFT)  and grant the software 
maker a non-exclusive license to its retained patent portfolio 
for about $1.056 billion in cash. He speaks on Bloomberg 
Television's "Inside Track." (Source: Bloomberg)  Running Time: 01:15
 